other_tests.findings: The appendix appears distended up to 8 mm with surrounding fat stranding. There is no evidence of rupture or fluid collections. There is no free air or free fluid throughout the abdomen. Mild bibasilar atelectasis noted. The remainder of the stomach and visualized loops of small and large bowel are within normal limits. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, bilateral adrenal glands, and bilateral kidneys are within normal limits. No mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy. The abdominal aorta is normal in caliber and contour. The bladder, distal ureters, uterus, ovaries, sigmoid colon, and rectum are within normal limits. No free fluid or free air throughout the pelvis. No pelvic or inguinal lymphadenopathy.
